snippet.textDisplay:
Vardy and de Bruyne could have made it too to be fair. Vardy has been almost regularly an outstanding striker in the last half of the decade. And de Bruyne too as a midfielder. Also won 2 PL titles as a very, if not the most, important ingredient of a ManCity side who absolutely dominated the league in ways we had never seen before. And this is coming from a ManUtd fan.

Although I don’t really disagree on anyone who actually made it into the XI. I would say decade-wise, Vardy and Van Persie's claims are similar. Kane, although didn’t win any trophy, is just better than both and deserves to be in this team. De Bruyne if you compare with Hazard and Silva wouldn’t make it because their respective longevities on the very upper echelon of PL football.

snippet.textDisplay:
My team:

GK: DDG
DF: Kompany, Koscielny, Kante
Koscielny has been one of the most consistent defenders of the decade and the lynchpin of arsenal's defense for most of it, unlike vidic/ferdinand who were great for the first 2-3 years or vandijk who only really showed his worth in the last 2-3 years.
Kante is the best DM in the league, but due to the congestion in midfield he drops into defence on my team
MF: Silva, Toure
CAM: Cazorla
Best Arsenal Midfielder of the decade, the team falls apart every time he is injured, imo super underrated
LW: Hazard
RW: Sterling
Had a great few seasons w/ Liverpool, almost winning w/ Suarez, and got even better after moving to ManCity
ST: Aguero, Kane

Didnt include ferdinand/vidic/rooney/rvp because man utd fell apart after ferguson left, which was very early in the decade
Didnt include kdb/vandijk/salah/firmino/mane because they only really shot to prominence in the final ~3 years of the decade
most shoddy picks would be koscielny and kane imo.
